description: Real Time raw data quality monitoring for DUNE ND 2x2 detector

panels.description: Mean over 10s of data rates (expressed as packet count per second) by pixel. Y-axis is log base 2. Yellow / Red thresholds = 1 / 5 p/s
panels.title: Chip $chip . Tile $tile . P$pacman: Data Rate (10s Mean)

panels.description: Invalid parity indicates that bits flipped at some point in the packet's transmission from chip to pacman. Invalid Parity % = sum (invalid parity) / sum (total) for each 10s interval. Y-axis is log base 2. Yellow threshold is 1%, Red threshold is 10%.
panels.title: Chip $chip . Tile $tile . P$pacman:  Invalid % (10s Mean)

panels.description: Configuration Rate: Max over 1s interval. Config packets should only appear while configuring ADCs. In a normal run mode, the appearance of configuration packets indicates a problem, such as a misconfigured chip or bits that flipped in transmission. Y-axis is log base 2. Thresholds are set for normal run mode as Yellow / Red = .1 p/s / .2 p/s
panels.title: Chip $chip . Tile $tile . P$pacman: Config Rate (1s max)

panels.description: Green bars are centered at Pixel-level Mean ADC value, the top/bottom of the bars are at Mean +/- RMS. All values are calculated over a 10s window.  Red thresholds are < 5 or > 254. Yellow threshold is 250
panels.title: Chip $chip . Tile $tile . P$pacman:  ADC Mean & RMS (10s Mean)

panels.description: Histogram shows distribution of Pixel-level ADC 10s mean values over the global time window. The bucket size is 1. ADC values are recorded using 8 bits. A value of 255 indicates the signal maxed out. Consistent 255 values (or consistent values below 5) may mean the threshold is set too high (or too low). Both problematic threshold cases could result in missing information.
panels.title: Chip $chip . Tile $tile . P$pacman: Mean ADC Distribution

panels.description: FIFO > 1/2 (or Full) is the fraction of times the FIFO was more than half full (or Full) divided by the total number of observations over a 10s window. "Shared" FIFO is calculated at the chip level. This graph shows the mean chip level ratio for the entire system. This stacked bar chart shows the FIFO > 1/2 (but not completely full) as a blue bar. On top of the blue bar is FIFO full shown as a red bar. Yellow / Red Threshold = 0.1 / 0.21
panels.title: Chip $chip . Tile $tile . P$pacman: Local FIFO > 1/2 and Full (10s Max)

panels.description: Filter Tables allow the user to sort up or down on any particular metric (i.e. column). The result will show the other metric maximums for that same pixel. The time window is 5 minutes.
